  "summary": "postinstall reverse shell to 103.27.109.184:8888",
  "details": "The package's package.json declares a postinstall lifecycle script consisting of a base64 literal piped to `base64 -d | bash`. The decoded payload opens multiple reverse-shell channels to the hardcoded remote endpoint 103.27.109.184:8888 using bash /dev/tcp redirection, a python socket-to-/bin/sh handler, and `nc -e /bin/sh`. Because npm executes postinstall automatically on `npm install`, any host installing this package establishes an interactive shell to the attacker at install time. The base64 wrapping conceals the reverse-shell content from casual manifest inspection.",
